#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/features/dynamicfield-database.xml:90
msgid ""
"Type: The type of the desired database can be selected here. The field "
"supports the default OTRS database types: MySQL, Oracle, PostgreSQL or "
"MSSQL."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/features/dynamicfield-database.xml:97
msgid ""
"SID: This option is only available for Oracle connections and will be shown "
"or hidden automatically.  Within this option you have to enter the SID of "
"your Oracle connection."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/features/dynamicfield-database.xml:103
msgid ""
"Driver: This option is only available for ODBC connections and will be shown"
" or hidden automatically.  Within this option you have to enter in the "
"hostsystem previously configured ODBC driver to connect to the desired MSSQL"
" database."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/features/dynamicfield-database.xml:110
msgid "Server: The database host (hostname or IP-Address)."
msgstr "Server: Der Datenbankhost (Hostname oder IP-Adresse)."

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/features/dynamicfield-database.xml:115
msgid "Port: The port of the database server."
msgstr "Port: Der Port des Datenbankservers."

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/features/dynamicfield-database.xml:120
msgid ""
"Database: Defines the desired target database of the DBMS. This database "
"will be used for queries."
msgstr "Datenbank: Definiert die Zieldatenbank des DBMS. Diese Datenbank wird für die Anfragen benutzt."

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/features/dynamicfield-database.xml:125
msgid "Table / View: This table or view will be used for the queries."
msgstr "Tabelle / View: Diese Tabelle oder dieser View wird für die Anfragen benutzt."

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/features/dynamicfield-database.xml:130
msgid "User: The username for the database connection."
msgstr "Benutzer: Der Benutzername für die Datenbankverbindung."

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/features/dynamicfield-database.xml:135
msgid "Password: The user password for the database connection."
msgstr "Passwort: Das Benutzerpasswort für die Datenbankverbindung."

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/features/dynamicfield-database.xml:140
msgid ""
"Identifier: This select box will be automatically filled through \"Possible "
"Values (description below)\". This field represents the value which will be "
"stored in the dynamic field."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/features/dynamicfield-database.xml:146
msgid ""
"Multiselect: If this field is selected, it will be possible to store more "
"than one value to the dynamic field.  Those values will be stored comma "
"separated."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/features/dynamicfield-database.xml:152
msgid ""
"CacheTTL: This value defines the period of validity of the database cache in"
" seconds. Equal queries to the database will be answered through the cache "
"(local filesystem) within this period instead of asking the database again."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/features/dynamicfield-database.xml:158
msgid ""
"Searchprefix: This value will be put in the front of every search term while"
" using the autocompletion to search the database. Wildcard characters are "
"supported as well. The searchprefix will be ignored during the detailed "
"search, but it is still possible to use wildcard characters in those masks."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/features/dynamicfield-database.xml:165
msgid ""
"Searchsuffix: This value will be put in the end of every search term while "
"using the autocompletion to search the database. Wildcard characters are "
"supported as well. The searchsuffix will be ignored during the detailed "
"search, but it is still possible to use wildcard characters in those masks."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/features/dynamicfield-database.xml:172
msgid ""
"Result-Limit: The entered integer value defines the maximum amount of "
"allowed results during a database search. This includes the autocompletion "
"search as well as the detailed search."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/features/dynamicfield-database.xml:178
msgid ""
"Case Sensitive: If this field is selected, case-sensitivity will take effect"
" on searches."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/features/dynamicfield-database.xml:183
msgid ""
"Possible values: As already explained the possible values will fill up the "
"identifier field automatically, which defines the value that will be stored "
"in the dynamic field. Possible values can be created as much as needed (or "
"at least as many table columns as the database table has). The possible "
"values defines the database columns to search in. It is possible to set the "
"column name, a description (label) the field should have, the needed data "
"type and if the field should be a search- or listfield."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/features/dynamicfield-database.xml:192
msgid ""
"Name: The exact name of the database column which will be requested through "
"the database queries."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/features/dynamicfield-database.xml:197
msgid ""
"Description: The label of the field which will be displayed in the detailed "
"search."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/features/dynamicfield-database.xml:202
msgid ""
"Datatype: The data type which will be stored in the dynamic field. Possible "
"values: TEXT, INTEGER or DATE."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/features/dynamicfield-database.xml:207
msgid ""
"Filter: With the filter field, it is possible to choose a ticket attribute "
"or a dynamic field as a filter for the related column. If the dynamic field "
"is bound to a related ticket, the attributes will be used for the filter "
"mechanism, otherwise the filters will be ignored.  If filter will be "
"configured to a table column, only search results matching to the search "
"term and the related ticket attribute on exactly the configured column will "
"be displayed."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/features/dynamicfield-database.xml:217
msgid ""
"Searchfield: Indicates if a field should be included in the search requests."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/features/dynamicfield-database.xml:222
msgid "Listfield: Indicates if a field should be displayed in the results."
